I had a really good time when I visited this bar for the first time during the 2018 Kwanzaa Crawl and decided to check it out on a Friday. The place was still filling up when I got there and the DJ had no musical vision, but these were the least of my . The bartenders misplaced my DEBIT CARD. I waited 15 minutes as the bartenders searched for it and when they could not find it I took down her number and decide to return they next day. That night I got an email from chase alerting me of some recent transactions that I did not make. Long story short, use cash when going to this establishment. They might just hand her debit card over to a stranger.

If you're socially minded, it's named after the great artist Jean-Michel Basquiat - an artist known for contrasting social injustice issues. He was lost to the 27 club when he over-dosed on heroine. This bar also hosts events related to the issues Basquiat fought to expose.

I absoultely love this place it’s so eclectic, yet grown & sexy and so soulful in its ambiance. I haven’t tried the food as of yet although I’ve heard rave reviews especially about their Meatballs stuffed with the Mozzarella. I love that the owner is very hands on I’ve been there and actually conducted a brief introduction conversation with her and she was ever so pleasant and inviting. I celebrated New Years Eve there at their “We Gotta Have It” black culture party, where my cousins and I experienced a night full of nostalgic music that really took us back to the times that this Bar & Lounge embodies and reignites within this community of Bed Stuy Brooklyn. I’ll definitely be a regular patron here and in fact will be stopping in this week to talk business as far as hosting my friend and I joint bday party at the establishment on St. Patty’s Day. We’re doing a Green & Gold theme should be fun right? #certifiedbycarter 👌🏾
